&lt;h2 id="install-the-splunk-otel-collector"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Install the Splunk OTel Collector&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#install-the-splunk-otel-collector" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="https://github.com/signalfx/splunk-otel-collector-chart" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Splunk OTel Collector Helm chart&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 is the production way to deploy the collector to Kubernetes. It handles the collector deployment, service, and configuration automatically.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Enable OBI via Helm</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/5-kubernetes/3-add-obi-daemonset/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/5-kubernetes/3-add-obi-daemonset/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Now add tracing to the entire cluster without changing any application code just one Helm upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="upgrade-the-collector-with-obi-enabled"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Upgrade the Collector with OBI Enabled&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#upgrade-the-collector-with-obi-enabled" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;helm -n obi-workshop upgrade splunk-otel-collector &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; splunk-otel-collector-chart/splunk-otel-collector &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --set&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;splunkObservability.realm=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;REALM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --set&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;splunkObservability.accessToken=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;ACCESS_TOKEN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --set&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;clusterName=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;INSTANCE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;-k8s&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --set&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;environment=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;INSTANCE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;-ebpf&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --set&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;obi.enabled=true&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That single &lt;code&gt;--set=&amp;quot;obi.enabled=true&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; is the only change. The Helm chart handles everything else:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. How This Scales</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/5-kubernetes/4-how-this-scales/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/5-kubernetes/4-how-this-scales/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="the-pattern-across-environments"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;The Pattern Across Environments&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#the-pattern-across-environments" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Phase 0 you ran a binary. In Phase 2 (Docker), you added one container. In Phase 3 (K8s), you ran one &lt;code&gt;helm upgrade&lt;/code&gt;. The pattern is the same:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Environment&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;OBI Deployment&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;What Changes&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Bare host&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Binary via &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Nothing: OBI watches processes from the kernel&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Docker Compose&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;One container&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Add a service to &lt;code&gt;docker-compose.yaml&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Kubernetes&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Helm chart flag&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;helm upgrade&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;--set=&amp;quot;obi.enabled=true&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="https://github.com/signalfx/splunk-otel-collector-chart/blob/main/docs/zero-code-ebpf-instrumentation.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Splunk OTel Collector Helm chart&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 is the production way to deploy both the collector and OBI. For even more automation, the &lt;a href="https://opentelemetry.io/docs/kubernetes/operator/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;OpenTelemetry Operator&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 can inject OBI as a sidecar automatically using annotations.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>